All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
CheckoutButton
Represents a button that allows the cashier to check out the current order and complete the transaction.
CheckoutPanel
Represents a panel containing a checkout button, allowing the cashier to finalize the order and complete the transaction.
databaseConnection
Class for connecting to the database and creating queries for the data tables
HomeUI
HomeUI class represents the main user interface of the application.
ItemButton
Represents a button corresponding to a menu item for adding it to the current order.
ItemTab
ItemTab class represents a tab in the menu that contains a list of menu items within a specific series, such as "Milk Foam Series," "Milk Tea Series," etc.
ManagmentTab
ManagmentTab class represents a tab within the management panel, displaying data from the database.
MenuItems
MenuItems class provides a representation of menu items from various series of drinks.
OrderItem
OrderItem class represents a single item in an order, such as "Taro Milk Tea" or "Black Tea." It includes information about the item's ID, name, size, price, quantity, toppings, ice level, sugar level, series, and ingredients.
OrderList
OrderList class represents a list of items in an order.
OtherTab
Represents the "Other" tab, which includes toppings and order modification options.
RemoveItemButton
Represents a button that removes a menu item from the current order.
ReportTab
Represents a panel for generating various reports and displaying them.
RestockQuantities
This class provides a static method to retrieve a HashMap of restock quantities for various inventory items.
ToppingButton
Represents a button that corresponds to a topping, allowing the user to add the topping to the current order.
